    "body": "I think the signature check is OK actually, because it uses the exit's internal epoch:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/a53830fd60a119bf3f659b253360af8027128e83/consensus/state_processing/src/per_block_processing/signature_sets.rs#L390-L395\r\n\r\nBut the other checks relative to current epoch are liable to fail, e.g.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/a53830fd60a119bf3f659b253360af8027128e83/consensus/state_processing/src/per_block_processing/verify_exit.rs#L46-L53\r\n\r\nPlumbing an optional wall-clock epoch into `verify_exit` could be one way to verify future exits from the current head state",
